    "body" : "<p>Just use the apache commons codec library. They have a utility class called <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/codec/apidocs/org/apache/commons/codec/digest/DigestUtils.html#sha%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\">DigestUtils</a></p>\n\n<p>No need to get into details.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 297453,
      "reputation" : 141,
      "user_id" : 602991,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ca4960b638efc7be1523119deccf25aa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "abhihere",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/602991/abhihere"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1320262148,
    "last_edit_date" : 1320262148,
    "creation_date" : 1296886827,
    "answer_id" : 4905469,
    "question_id" : 4895523,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Convert byte array to hex string.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String toSHA1(byte[] convertme) {\n    final char[] HEX_CHARS = \"0123456789ABCDEF\".toCharArray();\n    MessageDigest md = null;\n    try {\n        md = MessageDigest.getInstance(\"SHA-1\");\n    }\n    catch(NoSuchAlgorithmException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n    byte[] buf = md.digest(convertme);\n    char[] chars = new char[2 * buf.length];\n    for (int i = 0; i &lt; buf.length; ++i) {\n        chars[2 * i] = HEX_CHARS[(buf[i] &amp; 0xF0) &gt;&gt;&gt; 4];\n        chars[2 * i + 1] = HEX_CHARS[buf[i] &amp; 0x0F];\n    }\n    return new String(chars);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
