  "title" : "Java String to SHA1",
  "body" : "<p>I'm trying to make a simple String to SHA1 converter in Java and this is what I've got...</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String toSHA1(byte[] convertme) {\n    MessageDigest md = null;\n    try {\n        md = MessageDigest.getInstance(\"SHA-1\");\n    }\n    catch(NoSuchAlgorithmException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    } \n    return new String(md.digest(convertme));\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When I pass it <code>toSHA1(\"password\".getBytes())</code>, I get <code>[�a�ɹ??�%l�3~��.</code> I know it's probably a simple encoding fix like UTF-8, but could someone tell me what I should do to get what I want which is <code>5baa61e4c9b93f3f0682250b6cf8331b7ee68fd8</code>? Or am I doing this completely wrong?</p>\n"
}